(47, 1, '2025-06-12 07:45:24', '2025-06-12 07:45:24', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Aprilia Racing CEO Massimo Rivola has expressed the team‚Äôs commitment to repairing its fractured relationship with Jorge Martin following Marco Bezzecchi‚Äôs impressive British Grand Prix win‚ÄîAprilia‚Äôs first MotoGP victory of the season.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Martin, the reigning world champion and marquee signing for Aprilia‚Äôs new 2025 line-up, has had a disastrous start with the Noale-based factory. A string of injuries and crashes has restricted the Spaniard to just one grand prix appearance so far, while growing off-track tensions‚Äîespecially concerning a rumored performance-related exit clause‚Äîhave only heightened speculation around his future with the team.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Rivola addressed the situation after Bezzecchi‚Äôs win, emphasizing that Aprilia remains open to reconciliation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>‚ÄúWe are waiting for him,‚Äù said Rivola. ‚ÄúOur mission is to provide the best possible bike so when he returns, it‚Äôs ready to win. Today we showed the bike can win, but we have to do it more often.‚Äù</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Rivola also acknowledged the physical and emotional toll Martin‚Äôs recovery has taken.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>‚ÄúWhen you spend most of your time in a hospital bed, suffering, nobody truly knows how hard it is,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúRiders are meant to be on the bike‚Äînot at home recovering. We must respect that.‚Äù</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He admitted that much of the tension has come from conversations happening publicly instead of privately, saying:<br>‚ÄúThat‚Äôs not the right way. There are better ways to solve things, but it‚Äôs always difficult when both sides feel distant.‚Äù</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If Martin does return, Rivola made it clear that rebuilding trust will be essential.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>‚ÄúOne step at a time. First, we need him to come back. Then we work on trust,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúLike in a marriage, both sides must play their part. We‚Äôre ready to do ours.‚Äù</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Rivola also praised Bezzecchi not only for securing the win but for his leadership during challenging times.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>‚ÄúThis period has been so difficult, it‚Äôs something you couldn‚Äôt even write in a book,‚Äù Rivola said, referencing Martin‚Äôs string of injuries‚Äîduring testing, training, and then his brief return in Qatar.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He credited Bezzecchi‚Äôs dedication and positivity as a motivating force:<br>‚ÄúAfter the last race, Marco sent a video to the whole company saying, ‚ÄòI believe in the project, keep pushing.‚Äô That kind of message really drives everyone.‚Äù</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Still, Rivola remained grounded:<br>‚ÄúThere‚Äôs a saying in Italy‚Äîone bird doesn‚Äôt make spring. But at least we‚Äôve proven something to ourselves. When you go through tough times, you start to question your direction. This result is a boost for everyone at Noale who has been working day and night.‚Äù</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He admitted luck played a part, with Fabio Quartararo retiring from the lead due to a ride-height issue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>‚ÄúBut that‚Äôs racing,‚Äù Rivola added. ‚ÄúIt was great to see Marco take control and open up a four-second gap. I couldn‚Äôt be happier‚Äîespecially with our big Aprilia All Stars celebration coming up in Misano.‚Äù</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Jorge Martin is expected to attend the Misano event on June 1, alongside Aprilia‚Äôs MotoGP line-up.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Aprilia Willing to Heal Rift With Jorge Martin After Bezzecchi‚Äôs British GP Triumph', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-06-12 07:45:24', '2025-06-12 07:45:24', '', 1, 'http://127.0.0.1/eu9-international/?p=47', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(48, 1, '2025-06-12 08:08:39', '2025-06-12 08:08:39', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Marc Marquez described his crash during the initial start of the British Grand Prix as feeling ‚Äúlike a water park,‚Äù after an unusual incident saw him slide into a foam block at the Becketts chicane.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Ducati Lenovo Team rider lost control and hit one of the foam barriers designed to slow down riders who run wide before rejoining the track at Chapel. Despite the impact, Marquez downplayed the severity of the crash.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>‚ÄúIt was like a water park,‚Äù Marquez joked in the post-race press conference. ‚ÄúI was sliding but saw a wall. I knew it was soft. When I saw the impact, you need to be strong. It was after a crash, but this moment is not scary. You know that you will stop.‚Äù</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Marquez‚Äôs luck turned when the red flag was waved moments later due to a separate incident involving Franco Morbidelli and Aleix Espargaro, which caused fluid to spill on the circuit. Since the stoppage occurred before the end of lap three, the race was restarted in full‚Äîallowing Marquez to rejoin the grid despite his crash.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>‚ÄúI was the luckiest rider today because the red flag gave me a second chance,‚Äù he admitted.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Although he went on to finish on the podium, Marquez wasn‚Äôt satisfied with how the second part of the race unfolded, revealing that a tyre change negatively affected his performance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know why, but we changed tyres in the second race. The feeling in the second race was a disaster,‚Äù he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Marc Marquez Calls British GP Crash ‚ÄúLike a Water Park‚Äù After Lucky Restart', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'marc-marquez-calls-british-gp-crash-like-a-water-park-after-lucky-restart', '', '', '2025-06-12 09:48:00', '2025-06-12 09:48:00', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/eu9-international/?p=48', 0, 'post', '', 0),
